  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "I would like to be able to directly test private and internal methods of contracts using the hardhat test runner.\r\n\r\nOne possible way to implement this could be to convert `internal` and `private` methods in the contracts to `public`, internally, only when running `npx hardhat test`, so that unit tests can be written for functions that can't be accessed otherwise.\r\n\r\nIt doesn't seem to be a way around this other than always using `internal` rather than `private` and also writing a mock contract that inherits the `internal` and makes it public. Hardhat should be able to do something like that for the developer and inject it in the `ethers` contract object during unit tests.",
